Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I think the approach in patchset 1 might be better after all. Image ids that aren't uuid-like aren't really invalid I think, they just don't exist.

I think there was an important note on patchset1 that said there are several other places in glance.db.sqlalchemy.api where we do query.filter_by(uuid-like-column == 'blah') that probably need to be handled as well.

What is the timeline for fixing this bug in upstream db2?

Patch Set 7:

A few key points that came up in discussion:

1) Image ids don't really have to be uuids, they just have to be strings. It is an implementation detail that when we generate them we use uuids. If a different algorithm came along and demanded a different string format, we would switch to it. This is part of the HTTP API as it stands today in v1 and v2 and we should not break that interface. For this reason, non-uuid-like ids are not Invalid.

2) It seems like it might be cleaner to implement this as a length check inside the sqlalchemy api module. This would make sense, because we know from the models that the length of the id string is limited. This approach might save us having to use really specific DB data error strings in our exception handling, which is admittedly a bit gross.

Cheers!

Patch Set 7:

Thanks markwash help put our discussing result here.

I think/agree:

1. Always raise NotFound exception but a new exception for invalid image id, this can prevent to break backward-compatibility. Thanks Mark to raise this point up.

2. Check "len(id) > 36" only is work for me.

2. Put pre-checking logic in api level or db level is both fine. But TBH I still consider if we do pre-check in API level we can do more things when we needed in future.

Patch Set 7:

Guys, thanks a lot for your reviewing and good comments on this tiny patch. Based on above discussion, I'm going to take this way:

1. Only check if the image id is 36 chars for now
2. Check is placed at the API level
3. Return 404 instead of 400 to keep backward compatibility

Please let me know if you have any concern. Thanks.

Patch Set 11: (2 inline comments)

I think this patch still needs to shrink in scope. In my view, this patch should have as its only goal making the sqlalchemy db api work with db2. It is wrong for us to change our interfaces in the process. Changing the interfaces creates churn and instability that is not warranted by or truly necessary for the goal of incorporating db2.

If you take the latest patchset and simply remove the new exception type (stick with NotFound), and then remove all of the changes that were caused by the addition of the new exception type, then we will arrive at the best patch.

I'm not sure if there is a good way we can test it. Perhaps for now the right way is to add a particular unit test for the case of id > 36 to glance/tests/functional/db/test_sqlalchemy.py (despite the fact that this is supposedly a functional testing suite. . . hmm)
